Date: 0/0/1959
Source: Gun in My Hand, A
Author: SLATTER
Vol / Page: 219
Edition:
Quote: `A real Pommie eh? Imagine that.' `Yes, we're all Pommies here.' `A real bloody Pongo.' `This Pongo business annoys me. You haven't even got it right. Pongo's the naval word for soldiers or marines. Out here they use it as just another form of Pommie.' `Oh well, it's all the same to me.' ... `They're all right really. The Pommies, I mean. The Homeys, the Chooms, the Pongos.'
